# Secure Blockchain-Based Voting System (Hackathon Prototype)

## 1. Problem Statement
Traditional voting systems—whether paper-based or centralized electronic machines—suffer from several critical flaws:
- **Vote Tampering & Data Manipulation:** Centralized databases are vulnerable to hacking and insider threats.
- **Lack of Transparency:** Voters have no verifiable way to ensure their vote was counted accurately without trusting a central authority.
- **Inefficiency & Slow Results:** Manual counting or disjointed electronic systems can take days to finalize results.
- **Voter Suppression & Fraud:** Risks of duplicate voting, ballot stuffing, and unauthorized access diminish trust in the democratic process.

A secure, verifiable, and transparent digital voting system is needed to restore trust while bringing modern efficiency to the process.

## 2. Proposed Solution
We propose a **Blockchain-Based Voting Platform** designed as a tamper-proof, transparent, and secure prototype. 

For the context of this hackathon prototype, we will focus strictly on the **core logic and workflow** of blockchain voting. We will bypass real-world identity integrations (like Aadhaar/SSN verification) and instead use a simulated verified-user database. 

Pre-registered users will log in, cast their vote via an intuitive interface, and the backend will encode this action as a transaction on the blockchain. Once the transaction is mined into a block, the vote is permanent, immutable, and reflected in real-time.

